Linux Commands Fedora

Alt + f2;  gnome-terminal


 ls - l -a -t;  -l(long listing), -a(show hidden  dot files), -t(list by time)


type bash; - To determine the location of a particular command.


$ ls /usr/bin | sort -f | less; - This command lists the contents of the /usr/bin directory.


vi $(find /home | grep xyzzy);  - If you know the name but not the location of the file.


